'''''Guns of the Black Witch''''' ({{lang-it|'''Il terrore dei mari'''}}) is a 1961 [[adventure film]] directed by [[Domenico Paolella]].<ref name="60s">{{cite book|author1=Roberto Chiti |author2=Roberto Poppi |author3=Enrico Lancia |author4=Mario Pecorari |title=Dizionario del cinema italiano. I film|publisher=Gremese Editore, 1992|isbn=8876055932}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|last=Leonard Maltin|title=Leonard Maltin's Movie and Video Guide|publisher=Plume, 1995}}</ref>

It was released in the US by [[American International Pictures]] as a [[double feature]] with ''[[Lost Battalion (1962 film)|Lost Battalion]]''.

== Cast ==

* [[Don Megowan]]: Jean
* [[Silvana Pampanini]]: Delores 
* [[Emma Danieli]]: Elisa 
* [[Livio Lorenzon]]: Guzman 
* [[Germano Longo]]: Michel 
* [[Loris Gizzi]]: Governor 
* [[Philippe Hersent]]: Jean's Stepfather

==Release==
''Guns of the Black Witch'' was released in Italy on 24 February 1961.{{sfn|Kinnard|Crnkovich|2017|p=77}} It was released in the United States in December 1961.{{sfn|Kinnard|Crnkovich|2017|p=77}}

==Reception==
The ''[[Monthly Film Bulletin]]'' declared the film to be a "very tepid affair" and that "even the Caribbean looks unenticing in this representation, and Paolella's direction makes heavy weather of the action."<ref name="mfb-review">{{cite magazine|title=Terrore dei mari, Il (Guns of the Black Witch)|magazine=[[Monthly Film Bulletin]]|volume=30|issue=348|page=10|year=1963|publisher=[[British Film Institute]]}}</ref>

